<br>
Few other things from memory -<br>
<br>
(1)   Resists (especially MR) are important on this guy because he FEARS.  This guy is not a pushover like our friendly CS dragon was.  If you don't have the resists, some of us may have some to lend out.  I know I have a couple of resists folks might be able to wear.<br>
<br>
(2)  His AoE is frontal only.<br>
<br>
(3)  He will also go after anyone who sits, so NO SITTING during the fight (unless you're the MA).<br>
<br>
(4)  If I remember right, the turn in guy is a 5-hour spawn, so if he's not up, you'll have to find out when he was last killed.  Might be wise to track there before we start zoning in to get this answer.  There's not much to do nearby if we wait.<br>
<br>
Boraf and I have been involved in his fights, so we know what to expect.<br>
<br>
(5)  Two tactics I've seen or heard him done with - typical layout is casters far away from the melee (out of aggro range).  Second tactic which has worked is have casters in the tunnel, melee on the beach but the MA gets the mob turned around so the mob is facing the water not the tunnel.<br>
<br>
(6)  I'd plan for more than 3 groups if we can nab them.  You will want as many clerics as are on, and all of our pallies.  Don't hesitate to call in friends - the pallies generally do a chain LoH and shout when the last one has been used so the clerics and everyone else can start healing the MA.  Healers should be focused on the MA primarily/only.  Keeping him and SA alive is KEY to the success.  If they die, the mob tends to bounce around via aggro list and kill everyone with his AoE while he melee's the &quot;special ones&quot; hehe.<br>
<br>
***<br>
